content:
This file provides utility functions for managing CSS class names, primarily for use with Tailwind CSS and clsx.

## Key Exports

### `cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]): string`

A utility function that combines and merges CSS class names. It uses `clsx` to conditionally join class names and `tailwind-merge` to resolve overlapping Tailwind CSS classes.

#### Usage

```typescript
// Example usage with conditional classes
const isActive = true;
const className = cn(
  'px-4 py-2 rounded-md',
  isActive && 'bg-blue-500 text-white',
  !isActive && 'bg-gray-200 text-gray-700'
);

// className will be 'px-4 py-2 rounded-md bg-blue-500 text-white' if isActive is true
// className will be 'px-4 py-2 rounded-md bg-gray-200 text-gray-700' if isActive is false
```
